Cell.Data: The name of the GeoSciML or ERML element that this vocabulary is to be used for. (eg, Geologic History Relationship, Fault Type, Mineral Occurrence Type, Exploration Result, etc)

Terms to describe the surface, horizon, or time slice at which the mapped features occur (eg, surface geology, top of bedrock), as defined by the IUGS Commission for Geoscience Information (CGI) Geoscience Terminology Working Group. Adapted form the the INSPIRE vocabulary http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/codelist/MappingFrameValue. By extension, this vocabulary includes all concepts in this conceptScheme, as well as concepts in any previous versions of the scheme.

This file contains the 2017.01 version of the CGI Mapping Frame vocabulary. Vocabulary Shepherd: Mark Rattenbury. Compilation and review in Google doc spreadsheet, converted to MS Excel for SKOS generation using SKOS_for_GA_from_XLS_2016.03.xslt

Base of the predominantly unconsolidated sedimentary material of Quaternary age, also referred to as superficial deposits

Bedrock and predominantly unconsolidated sedimentary material of Quaternary age (superficial deposits) that would be visible if the overlying soil was removed or are exposed at the topographic surface.

The surface in the crust of the Earth below sedimentary or volcanic deposits, or tectonically transported rock unit. What constitutes basement can depend on the context and may comprise other sedimentary, igneous and/or metamorphic rocks.
Top surface of the usually solid rock that may either be exposed at the topographic surface or covered by other younger unconsolidated deposits of Quaternary age (superficial deposits)
